</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FEB4EF82FF81FFDBFF07FF26AD46FEAC" pageId="15" pageNumber="331" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="B611BC09FF81FFDBFF07FF26AD46FEAC" blockId="15.[151,1437,151,320]" pageId="15" pageNumber="331">
<emphasis id="84DA601BFF81FFDBFF07FF26AF50FF49" bold="true" box="[199,335,223,248]" pageId="15" pageNumber="331">Comments.</emphasis>
This species is distinguished by the 
<taxonomicName id="71AEC78AFF81FFDBFCD4FF26ADBAFF49" box="[788,933,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Heterospilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mesopleuron">mesopleuron</taxonomicName>
and scutellum smooth, mesoscutum lobes weakly granulate and the basal median areas weakly granulate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FEB4EF82FF81FFDBFF07FEDEAAFAFEF1" box="[199,1253,295,320]" pageId="15" pageNumber="331" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="B611BC09FF81FFDBFF07FEDEAAFAFEF1" blockId="15.[151,1437,151,320]" box="[199,1253,295,320]" pageId="15" pageNumber="331">
<emphasis id="84DA601BFF81FFDBFF07FEDEAF51FEF1" bold="true" box="[199,334,295,320]" pageId="15" pageNumber="331">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named in honour of the entomologist Alejandro Zaldívar-Riverón.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
